  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "So Zadok the priest, and Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada,.... The three men that David sent for on this occasion: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the Cherethites and the Pelethites; not the sanhedrim, as Ben Gersom, but David's guards, over whom Benaiah was: these ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "went down; from Jerusalem; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and caused Solomon to ride upon King David's mule; as he had ordered: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and brought him to Gihon; or Siloah, as the Targum; hence the Jews say (e), they do not anoint a king but at a fountain; but this is the only instance of it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(e) T. Bab. Ceritot, fol. 5. 2.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(e) T. Bab. Ceritot, fol. 5. 2.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
